  },
  "claim": "The unique compatible F2 parity cocycle on the finite Virasoro generator layer integrates to a certified central extension of the rank-10 kernel translation group. In the canonical section the extension has order 2048, center order 512, derived subgroup order 2, exponent 4, and group type D8 x C2^8. Its nonzero named commutators are exactly the paired cross-return composite triangle, and it admits a signed projective action on all 1024 kernel states.",
  "definition": {
    "central_cocycle": "c(x,y)=x_a y_b in F2.",
    "group_law": "(x,z)(y,t)=(x+y, z+t+c(x,y)).",
    "kernel_coordinates": "Use the eight primitive-preserving coordinates P0,P1,P2,P3,P4,P6,P7,P8 plus a=C5_9 and b=C5_10; C9_10 is represented by a+b.",
    "projective_kernel_action": "rho(x,z)|m> = (-1)^(z + x_a m_b) |m+x>, where m_b is the C5_10 coordinate of the state."
  },
